                            <comment id="14029943" author="cnauroth" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 22:36:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=benoyantony&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;benoyantony&quot;&gt;benoyantony&lt;/a&gt;.  I think it&apos;s a safe change.  I did some digging and traced back to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-2746&quot; title=&quot;[MR-279] [Security] Yarn servers can&amp;#39;t communicate with each other with hadoop.security.authorization set to true&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAPREDUCE-2746&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAPREDUCE-2746&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introducing the locking.  It was meant to fix a problem with &lt;tt&gt;ServiceLoader&lt;/tt&gt; lazily loading the real &lt;tt&gt;securityInfoProviders&lt;/tt&gt; and not implementing its own thread-safety.  It looks to me like the same pattern was applied to &lt;tt&gt;testProviders&lt;/tt&gt; for consistency, but it doesn&apos;t provide any real benefit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see the same thing in &lt;tt&gt;SecurityUtil#getTokenInfo&lt;/tt&gt;.  Do you want to change that one too?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
